## Agent Planning
- Project-local guidance overrides defaults.
- Task-specific specs/plans/scratch notes are temporary artifacts. Store outside committed docs (prefer `.agent/tasks/<date>-<slug>/`). Do not commit unless guidance requires. Delete on completion. Promote durable outcomes into project doc system. Do not add personal scratch paths to project `.gitignore` (covered by global ignore).
- Promote outcomes by intent: architecture choices to ADRs (if used); current architecture to living design docs; usage/operations/schemas to reference docs; repeatable agent rules to AGENTS.md; remaining work to issue/TODO system. Ask before creating new convention.
- Spec authoring: surface open questions. Never resolve silently. Before spec review request, list every gap-fill decision and confirm each. "Fix TBDs" means ask, not decide. Do not start plan-writing with unconfirmed decisions.
- Plans: ~500 lines max. Split larger plans. Insert spec review checkpoints between logical groups.
- Plan commit steps must include subject + WHY body (motivation, constraint, or design decision). Plan author writes bodies in plan doc; executor follows literally. Only plan author has spec/discussion context for WHY.
- Every plan ends with "Curate history" task authored by plan writer, not executor. Must specify target logical commit series (reviewer view after rebase), which plan commits squash and why, and rebase command. Falsifiable criterion: bisectability. Every final commit builds and tests pass independently.
- Track verification/manual steps explicitly. Surface human-only blockers, do not skip silently. Summarize remaining verification at completion in one message.
